author: Anonymous Poet
title: Check-Expect Errors
question:
Hi,
I'm working on an HtDF question and I keep getting this error: 
check-expect: expects only 2 arguments, but found 6
Does anyone have any suggestions on how I can fix this? I don't exactly understand what it means.
student_answer:
It's hard to give help or hints without seeing the code you're working on.
But from looking at the check-expect documentation: it seems likely that you have a missing parenthesis somewhere, so Racket thinks that the check-expect expression is much longer than it is.
